HEADWORD: Sinewed
<hw>Sin"ewed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Furnished
with sinews; <as>as, a strong-<ex>sinewed</ex> youth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: Equipped; strengthened.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When he sees⟦br⟧
Ourselves well <qex>sinewed</qex> to our defense.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinewiness</ent>⟦br⟧
